article.description: Matt Ryan registered 18 points as Chattanooga edged past Jacksonville State 63-60 in an Emerald Coast Classic bracket championship game on Saturday.
article.headline: Ryan carries Chattanooga past Jacksonville St. 63-60
article.linkText: Ryan carries Chattanooga past Jacksonville St. 63-60
article.story: NICEVILLE, Fla. -- Matt Ryan registered 18 points as Chattanooga edged past Jacksonville State 63-60 in an Emerald Coast Classic bracket championship game on Saturday. Jonathan Scott had 15 points for Chattanooga (5-3), including a go-ahead 3-pointer with 35 seconds left. David Jean-Baptiste iced it with two free throws and a Gamecocks' 3 at the buzzer missed. Jacara Cross had 19 points for the Gamecocks (2-4). Ty Hudson added 12 points. De'Torrion Ware had 7 points and 10 rebounds. Chattanooga matches up against Western Carolina on the road on Tuesday. Jacksonville State matches up against George Mason on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
